Ways to prevent sql injection 
  input validation
  least previlege to database
  WAF 
  database hardening 
  educating the developer about secure coding practices
what is cross-site scripting :
  Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) is a vulnerability that allows attackers to inject malicious scripts into web pages viewed by other users. These scripts execute in the context of the victim's browser, enabling the attacker to steal session cookies, hijack user sessions, deface websites, or perform other malicious actions.
ways to prevent cross-site scripting:
  input validation
  safer brwoser headers
  regualr security auditing like regular SAST,DAST,penetration test to adhere to OWASP secuity policies 

